Package zuul.gameState.maps

Class Map

java.lang.Object
zuul.gameState.maps.Map
Direct Known Subclasses:
ZuulMap
public abstract class Map
extends java.lang.Object
An abstract map of the game.

A concrete extension to this is a map of the game and represents the game state that is made up of every Room and Character that can be interacted with by the Game. An Item must be held by a Character or be in a Room so they are not represented by this class as a separate part of the game state.

    • createRooms

      protected abstract void createRooms()
      Creates every Room that is part of the initial game state.

      Every room should be fully instantiated with its initial state. This includes exits to other rooms and each Item the room holds. Fully instantiated rooms should then be added to this map to include them in the initial game state.

    • createCharacters

      protected abstract void createCharacters()
      Creates every Character that is part of the initial game state.

      Every character should be fully instantiated with its initial state. This includes its starting Room and each Item the character holds. Fully instantiated characters should then be added to this map to include them in the initial game state.

    • printWelcome

      public abstract void printWelcome()
      Prints a welcome message to the player.

      This should be called at the start of the game flow logic.

      This method should introduce the player to this Map.

      It is recommended that a prompt to type the 'help' command be printed in this method.
